    "text": "Salt exposure increased reactive oxygen species and osmolyte accumulation. Transcriptional reprogramming intensified with higher salinity. Network analysis identified eight regulatory layers corresponding to distinct salt stress stages. It revealed coordinated activation of ethylene and jasmonic acid signaling pathways. Lipid transfer proteins (VrLTPs) were induced under high-salt conditions. VrLTPs co-expressed with transcription factors WRKY, MYB, and NAC. VrLTPs likely function as regulators of late-stage stress adaptation.",
